Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered). Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel,
and finely chop @shallot{1}(finely chopped) until you have ¼ cup. Halve @orange{1}; squeeze
juice into a #small bowl{} until you have 2 TBSP. Peel and dice remaining orange into
½-inch pieces. Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}(peeled and pitted); dice into ½-inch
pieces. Squeeze juice from one lemon wedge over avocado and sprinkle with @salt{}. Finely
chop @chives{1/4%ounce}.

> Removing as much of the white pith from orange as possible reduces bitterness.
> Squeezing lemon juice on avocado keeps it from turning brown!

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.
Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, in a #small pot{}, combine chopped shallot, juice from one lemon
wedge, @white wine vinegar{2%tsp}, @water{1/3%cup}, and a pinch of @sugar{}. Bring to a
simmer, then reduce heat to medium. Cook until about 2 TBSP liquid remains, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use juice from two lemon wedges, 4 tsp vinegar, and 2/3 cup water.

While shallot mixture simmers, cut @cold butter{2%tbsp} into four pieces.

Once liquid has reduced in shallot mixture, reduce heat to low. Whisk in butter one piece
at a time, melting each piece before adding the next, until sauce is pale and creamy.

Remove pot from heat. Whisk in @crème fraîche{2%tbsp} until combined. Season with @salt{}
(we used ½ tsp) and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

> If sauce seems too thick, add water 1 tsp at a time.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon
to pan, skin sides down. Cook until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Remove pan from heat.

== Salad ==

Whisk @white wine vinegar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} into #bowl{} with orange juice.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Add a squeeze of lemon juice if you like a tangier dressing!

Combine @mixed greens{2%ounce}, avocado, and diced orange in a #medium bowl{}. Toss with
as much dressing as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Reheat sauce over low heat if needed.

> If sauce has thickened, add more water 1 tsp at a time.

Divide salmon, potatoes, and salad between plates. Spoon sauce over salmon. Top salad
with @walnuts{1/2%ounce}. Garnish salmon and potatoes with chives. Serve.